# Feature development

## Principles

- **No tech debt:** reuse existing services, handlers, keyboards, `texts.t`; no parallel implementations
- **Integrated & safe:** smallest correct diff; preserve business logic and upstream hot paths (`purchase.py`, `tariff_purchase.py`, `start.py`, `inline.py`, `texts.py`) unless the user asks otherwise
- **One concern per branch/commit** — see `delivery-cycle.mdc`

## Workflow

1. New branch from `main` — never commit features directly on `main`
2. Implement; agent smoke (`import main`)
3. Commit; push/PR when ready
4. **User smoke** (bot / cabinet / web as relevant)
5. Merge `dev-local` → `main` **only after explicit user approval** — see `git-branch-workflow.mdc`

Agent must **not** push/merge production without user approval.

## What kind of work?

| Type | Approach |
|------|----------|
| Custom feature (e.g. C2C) | `app/plugins/<name>/` + thin hooks — `custom-plugin-pattern.mdc` |
| Persian UI / strings | `localization-upstream.mdc` — not a plugin |
| User-visible currency label | `currency-display-toman.mdc` — not FX in the same commit |

## Definition of done

- [ ] Focused branch and commits
- [ ] No regressions; scope reviewed
- [ ] User smoke passed on relevant surfaces
- [ ] User approved PR → then merge
